<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F18FE9848A75121FE5BFDE7" lastPageId="344" lastPageNumber="345" pageId="342" pageNumber="343" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F18FE9648A75121FF67F825" blockId="342.[151,1436,1549,2005]" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F18FE9648A75121FE09F9D5" bold="true" box="[151,428,1549,1574]" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F18FE964A825121FCA8F9D5" box="[690,781,1549,1573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="342" pageNumber="343" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Head, antenna, prothorax and scutum testaceous; rest of mesosoma black, except posterior extremity of propodeum yellow; petiole black; metasoma testaceous, except tergite 1 partly brown. Antenna clavate. Head shiny, smooth, unsculptured, except occiput and part of vertex granulated; ocellar triangle strongly isosceles, with median longitudinal keel; OL much longer than POL. Palpal formula 5/2. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, with disc dull and granulated; anterior collar smooth, shiny and unsculptured; posterior edges of pronotum rounded, not produced into lobes. Scutum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated. Scutellum shiny, smooth, finely punctate. Metanotum very reduced and short. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keels; posterior surface without longitudinal keels. Fore wing of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38F18FE964AB25001FD43F8B5" box="[642,742,1837,1861]" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">holotype</typeStatus>
hyaline, without dark transverse bands; in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F18FE9648A7507DFF5AF899" box="[151,255,1873,1897]" name="Thailand" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, Maerim, fore wing with one dark transverse band. Protrochanter approximately four times as long as broad. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F18FE96499C5059FD94F87D" box="[428,561,1909,1933]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Plate 102C</figureCitation>
) with one subapical tooth and one row of five lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F18FE96492150B5FE35F841" box="[273,400,1945,1969]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="342" pageNumber="343">Plate 102C</figureCitation>
) with one row of about nine lamellae; distal apex with about nine lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/ 0/1.
</paragraph>
<caption id="54B656C98F19FE9748A75079FC72F837" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="343" pageNumber="344" startId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" targetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" targetPageId="343">
