<paragraph id="007606418F16FE9848F757BBFE5BFDE7" blockId="344.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="344" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F16FE9848F757BBFE65FF40" bold="true" box="[199,448,151,176]" pageId="344" pageNumber="345">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F16FE984AFD57BBFCFFFF5F" box="[717,858,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="344" pageNumber="345" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.6 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 5:4.5:7:8:8:8:7.5:8:7:9. Head swollen, shiny, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures; frontal line incomplete, only present in anterior half of face; occipital carina complete; temple very prominent; POL = 4; OL = 2; OOL = 4; OPL = 1; TL = 4.5; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli slightly longer than OPL (1.5:1). Palpal formula 5/3. Scutum finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated; minimum distance between notauli as long as greatest breadth of posterior ocelli. Scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Propodeum dull, completely reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein much longer than proximal part (14:6). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F16FE984AA656F0FCB0FE04" box="[662,789,476,500]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="344" pageNumber="345">Plate 102B</figureCitation>
) with inner dorsal fold-shaped process not showing any sense organs. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
